        FOBOFC_II                                                             = 7466,  -- fobOFC{[#[`II
        FOBO_U_D35E7B                                                         = 7467,  -- fobO%u*%d35E7B
        MY_SPIRIT_WAS_IMPRISONED_IN_DARKNESS_BUT_YOU                          = 7468,  -- My spirit was imprisoned in darkness, but you have released it! I am called Gerwitz, and you have my thanks.
        YOU_WILL_CERTAINLY_HELP_STOP_THE_BLADE_OF                             = 7469,  -- You will certainly help stop the blade of the dark god that wanders the Crystal Line and yearns to shed new blood!
        THE_WEAPONS_I_WROUGHT_ARE_NOW_FAR_FROM                                = 7470,  -- The weapons I wrought are now far from my formless hands, and have gained a will of their own. I forged the axe and sword that you defeated.
        BUT_MY_SCYTHE_HAS_LEFT_THIS_LAND_AND                                  = 7471,  -- But my scythe has left this land, and seeks even greater power. Should it find it, I fear for the lives of many!
        MY_SOUL_CANNOT_REST_IF_THINGS_ARE_LEFT                                = 7472,  -- My soul cannot rest if things are left like this!
        IS_THAT_REALLY_WHAT_S_KEEPING_YOU_HERE                                = 7473,  -- Is that really what's keeping you here, Gerwitz? You mean that the weapon gained a will of its own here in Ordelle all by itself?
        ZEID_HOW_WISE_YOU_HAVE_BECOME_I_HID                                   = 7474,  -- Zeid... How wise you have become! I hid myself when I felt you were near, but it seems you know everything.
        YOU_RE_RIGHT_ZEID_I_WANTED_MY_SOUL                                    = 7475,  -- You're right, Zeid. I wanted my soul to migrate, but the fear of losing these memories was too great.
        AND_THAT_S_WHY_YOU_ABANDONED_THE_PATH                                 = 7476,  -- And that's why you abandoned the path?
        NO_THAT_IS_NOT_ALL_THERE_ARE_TOO                                      = 7477,  -- No, that is not all! There are too few who can work with darksteel. All my work was in vain!
        I_BEGAN_TO_HATE_EVEN_RAOGRIMM_THE_TALEKEEPER                          = 7478,  -- I began to hate even Raogrimm the Talekeeper. I could not accept how everyone must lose all memory when they transmigrate over and over again, while only he inherited their memories. My feelings turned to a deep loathing that refused to leave this world, even after my departure.
        YOUR_SOUL_NO_LONGER_KNOWS_TIME_YOU_CANNOT                             = 7479,  -- Your soul no longer knows time. You cannot have known that Raogrimm is dead.
        AFTER_ALL_THINGS_ARE_DIFFERENT_NOW_THEY_SAY                           = 7480,  -- After all, things are different now. They say this is the age of adventurers. Some even wrought things of darksteel. All you accomplished did not go to waste.
        SO_THIRTY_YEARS_HAS_GONE_BY_THIS_QUICKLY                              = 7481,  -- So, thirty years has gone by this quickly...
        THAT_IS_RIGHT_OURS_IS_A_WORLD_FULL                                    = 7482,  -- That is right. Ours is a world full of pain and suffering, yet there is always hope. How foolish it was to become a prisoner to darkness and stop the flow of your soul's time.
        AND_I_HAVE_FOUND_AN_HEIR_TO_THE                                       = 7483,  -- And I have found an heir to the ways of darkness.
        HAH_HOW_YOU_VE_CHANGED_ZEID                                           = 7484,  -- Hah! How you've changed, Zeid.
        I_HAVE_ABSOLUTE_FAITH_THAT_HE_SHE_CAN                                 = 7485,  -- I have absolute faith that he/she] can shatter the blade of death.
        ADVENTURER_ARE_YOU_READY_TO_STARE_INTO_THE                            = 7486,  -- Adventurer, are you ready to stare into the face of death? Then, return whence you first were recognized as a follower of darkness.
        WAIT_ZEID_TELL_ME_THIS_HAS_THE_NEW                                    = 7487,  -- Wait, Zeid. Tell me this: has the new Talekeeper made himself known?
        YES_INDEED_THE_ONE_WHO_INHERITS_ALL_MEMORY                            = 7488,  -- Yes. Indeed, the one who inherits all memory has come.
        THEN_TELL_HIM_THIS_LEAD_OUR_PEOPLE_AWAY                               = 7489,  -- Then, tell him this: lead our people away from the pits of fear and hatred.
        ID_7490                                                               = 7490,  -- ...
        ADVENTURER_I_LEAVE_YOU_THIS_ARMOR_OF_MY                               = 7491,  -- Adventurer, I leave you this armor of my crafting. Please...stop the blade of the dark one!
        YOU_CANNOT_CARRY_ANY_MORE_TRY_AGAIN_LATER                             = 7492,  -- You cannot carry any more %. Try again later.
        YOU_RECEIVE_NOTHING_FROM_THE_MOON_RABBIT                              = 7493,  -- You receive nothing from the moon rabbit...
        THE_MOON_RABBIT_HAS_BROUGHT_ALONG_A_MONSTER                           = 7494,  -- The moon rabbit has brought along a monster!
        YOU_HAVE_TO_DO_SOMETHING_ABOUT_THOSE_CRAZY                            = 7495,  -- You have to do something about those crazy trees, kupo!
        YOU_RE_DONE_FIGHTING_TREES_KUPO                                       = 7496,  -- You're done fighting trees, kupo?
        THERE_IS_NOTHING_OUT_OF_THE_ORDINARY_HERE_2                           = 7504,  -- There is nothing out of the ordinary here.
        SOMETHING_ABOUT_THIS_PATCH_OF_GROUND_ALERTS_YOUR                      = 7505,  -- Something about this patch of ground alerts your thief instincts.
        YOU_NEED_TO_DIG_HERE                                                  = 7506,  -- You need % to dig here.
        THERE_IS_NOTHING_ELSE_OF_INTEREST_HERE                                = 7507,  -- There is nothing else of interest here.
        DIG_DIG_DIG_DIG                                                       = 7508,  -- (dig...dig...dig...dig)
        YOU_FIND_AN_OLD_CHEST                                                 = 7509,  -- You find an old chest!
        HOWEVER_YOUR_BREAKS                                                   = 7510,  -- However, your % breaks.
        HEY_WHAT_DO_YOU_THINK_YOU_RE_DOING                                    = 7511,  -- Hey! What do you think you're doing, finding the trrreasure chest before me!?
        RRRIGHT_MOVE_IT_OR_LOSE_IT_I_LL                                       = 7512,  -- Rrright, move it or lose it. I'll be the one to open it.
        THERE_MIGHT_BE_SOME_KINDA_NASTY_TRRRAP_JUST                           = 7513,  -- There might be some kinda nasty trrrap just waiting to spring on a kitten like you.
        RAUUUGH_GOT_IT_OPEN_NOW_LET_S_TAKE                                    = 7514,  -- ...Rauuugh! Got it open! Now, let's take a look at the treasure...
        HUH_THIS_IS_A_POOR_HAUL_SOME_MUSTY                                    = 7515,  -- ...Huh? This is a poor haul... Some musty old armor, some velvet mantles and...ah! A golden scepter! This will go for a good price!
        BUT_THIS_THIS_IS_NOT_WHAT_I_EXPECTED                                  = 7516,  -- But this... This is not what I expected at all... There's something strange going on here...
        WELL_WELL_IT_SEEMS_WE_HAVE_SOME_UNINVITED                             = 7517,  -- Well, well. It seems we have some uninvited guests...
        YOU_TWO_STAY_WHERE_YOU_ARE                                            = 7518,  -- You two! Stay where you are!
        I_VE_SEEN_THAT_FACE_BEFORE                                            = 7519,  -- I've seen that face before!
        WHO_WOULD_VE_THOUGHT_SOMEONE_WOULD_GET_HERE                           = 7520,  -- Who would've thought someone would get here before us?
        THERE_ARE_ONLY_TWO_OF_THEM_WE_SHOULD                                  = 7521,  -- There are only two of them... We should take care of this before it becomes a problem.
        WAIT_I_KNOW_THESE_PEOPLE_THEY_HELPED_ME                               = 7522,  -- Wait, I know these people. They helped me with a little task at the Tenshodo.
        I_THOUGHT_THIS_MIGHT_HAPPEN_BUT_FOR_THE                               = 7523,  -- I thought this might happen, but... For the two of you to make it this far, it would seem that not all thieves are totally incompetent these days.
        WOULD_YOU_MIND_INTRODUCING_YOUR_FRIENDS_TO_THE                        = 7524,  -- Would you mind introducing your friends to the rest of us, Vauderame?
        OF_COURSE_THIS_IS_NANAA_MIHGO_OF_WINDURST                             = 7525,  -- Of course. This is Nanaa Mihgo of Windurst, and %, an adventurer [of San d'Oria/of Bastok/also of Windurst].
        LINZAZA_YOU_MENTIONED_SOMEONE_ASKED_FOR_YOUR_SIGNATURE                = 7526,  -- Linzaza, you mentioned someone asked for your signature again. I'm assuming that that someone is standing before you now.
        YES_YOU_RE_RIGHTARU_I_NEED_TO_BE                                      = 7527,  -- Yes, you're rightaru. I need to be more of a villainy-willain, and start being suspicious of people.
        NOW_THAT_YOU_MENTION_IT_I_ROLLED_DICE                                 = 7528,  -- Now that you mention it, I rolled dice with [her/him].
        AND_THAT_MITHRA_OVER_THERE_WAS_THE_ONE                                = 7529,  -- And that Mithra over there was the one who came to my hideout.
        MORE_THAN_HALF_OF_US_HAVE_BEEN_UNMASKED                               = 7530,  -- ...More than half of us have been unmasked. I'm going to take care of this while there are no witnesses...
        YOU_FORGET_KANIKA_ATAREFAUNET_S_BAND_IS_NO                            = 7531,  -- You forget, Kanika. Atarefaunet's band is no more. We are now known as Vauderame's Knights.
        I_WAITED_TWENTY_YEARS_FOR_THE_FORMER_MARQUIS                          = 7532,  -- I waited twenty years for the former Marquis to remember everything. All that is left is to restore the glory of our lost kingdom.
        BUT_VAUDERAME_THESE_GUYS_HAVE_SEEN_WHAT_S                             = 7533,  -- But Vauderame, these guys have seen what's in the chest. If we don't knock 'em off now, there's bound to be trouble later.
        THE_ROYAL_SCEPTER_HAS_ALREADY_FOUND_ITS_WAY                           = 7534,  -- The royal scepter has already found its way into that Mithra's pocket. Even if her knowledge of its history is lacking, she still has a nose for value.
        NOT_ONE_OF_YOU_HAS_CHANGED_EVEN_AFTER                                 = 7535,  -- Not one of you has changed, even after all these years. Luckily, I was prepared for this.
        TAKE_CARE_OF_IT                                                       = 7536,  -- ...Take care of it.
        THIS_IS_ALL_OF_IT_VAUDERAME_THE_WHOLE                                 = 7537,  -- ...This is all of it, Vauderame. The whole set of knights' equipment is here, just as it used to be. The smell of the past still clings to it.
        IT_WILL_BE_GONE_BY_THE_TIME_WE                                        = 7538,  -- It will be gone by the time we reach Tavnazia. Mightaru be a good idea to lose that tummy-wummy on the way, as well.
        I_LL_GET_RID_OF_THE_RUST_I                                            = 7539,  -- I'll get rid of the rust. I brought the gear with me.
        ARE_YOU_SURE_ABOUT_THOSE_TWO_IT_S                                     = 7540,  -- ...Are you sure about those two? It's not like you to leave loose ends, even if their memory has been erased.
        MITHRA_MIGHT_SEEM_WILD_AND_FREE_BUT_THEY                              = 7541,  -- Mithra might seem wild and free, but they are deeply tied to one another. If we kill this one now, others will come looking for revenge. They will chase us to the ends of Vana'diel.
        THEN_THERE_IS_THIS_ADVENTURER_HE_SHE_LOOKS                            = 7542,  -- Then there is this adventurer. He/She] looks like someone I did away with in another time...
        SO_YOU_RE_GOING_TO_LEAVE_THAT_HERE                                    = 7543,  -- So you're going to leave that % here? It's almost as if you want him/her] to come after you.
        PERHAPS_YOU_RE_RIGHT_A_FOOTHOLD_INTO_THE                              = 7544,  -- ...Perhaps you're right. A foothold into the country I have spent twenty years restoring... Maybe my ego demands a witness to all that I have accomplished.
        VAUDERAME_WE_WILL_AWAIT_YOU_AND_THE_MARQUIS                           = 7545,  -- ...Vauderame. We will await you and the Marquis in our homeland.
        I_WILL_JOIN_YOU_AS_SOON_AS_I                                          = 7546,  -- I will join you as soon as I can. Let us meet again in a newborn country...
        MY_HOMELAND_TAVNAZIA                                                  = 7547,  -- My homeland, Tavnazia.
        HEY_THE_CATNAP_IS_OVER                                                = 7548,  -- Hey! The catnap is over!
        YOU_RE_FINALLY_UP_WE_WERE_CAUGHT_BY                                   = 7549,  -- You're finally up... We were caught by a trrrap on the treasure chest and sent into dreamland. It took me by surprise.
